parameters:
This is the automaton workshop. Creating automatons that
move on their own is my dream.

Oh, it seems you're out of smoke bombs? Take these newly
made smoke bombs with you.
Hello, Master Genkai. Are you available right now?

Oh, is that you, Karin-chan? You've come at just the right
time. The item you requested is complete.
Wow! The smoke bombs are finished, aren't they? Amazing!

When thrown, they break and smoke comes out. I've tested
them many times. They're a perfect creation, if I do say so
myself.

Thank you so much! I'm glad I asked you, Master Genkai, who
is skilled with mechanisms!

Ho ho ho. I am the best inventor in Edo, after all. Making
smoke bombs is a simple task for me. But still... what will
you use these for?

Well, that's... I've been prone to encountering perverts
lately... so it's for self-defense... ahaha...! (I can't say
that I'm going to use the smoke bombs for thieving...)

...Hmm. I've been watching over you since you were a child,
Karin-chan, and indeed, your figure has become more
voluptuous and alluring lately... It's only sensible to be
cautious against perverts.

Yes! Exactly! So with that said, I'll be taking the smoke
bombs with me! Thank you for making them!
Hmm. Take good care of the smoke bombs I made for you.
Hmm... I wonder if this is good enough.
Ah, is that you, Karin-chan? As lively as ever, I see.

Yes. It's a wooden horse. Not for children, but for adults.
Commonly known as a "triangle horse."

Since you've seen it, there's no helping it. Well, I'll tell
you specially because I trust you, Karin-chan. This was made
upon request.
Wow. You made it on request?

Indeed. It was a confidential request from a certain feudal
lord's family. Well, torture devices like triangle horses
are common, but this one was requested to move
automatically. I've finally completed it.
An automatically moving horse? That's an amazing mechanism.

Yes. It has a spring inside and is designed to move with a
clockwork mechanism... but there's one problem.

That's right. I haven't conducted any experiments using a
person yet. It's a confidential matter, so I can't ask just
anyone.
I see. So you haven't tested it with a person yet...

I would test it myself, but I'm an old man with back pain...
Honestly, I've been in quite a bind... (glances over)

Eh! Why are you looking at me? Don't tell me... Doctor, do
you want to put me on this and test it...?

Ho ho ho. You're sharp. I'd like to see if this horse
operates properly with Karin-chan riding it... Would you do
me the honor? I'll give you a reward of 2000 mon.

(...An experiment with a triangle horse, huh... What should
I do...)
Sure, why not. It sounds interesting.

What!? Are you serious? I thought for sure you'd refuse an
offer to be a test subject for a triangle horse!? Are you
truly alright with this?

Well... If all I have to do is ride it, and I get 2000 mon
for that, it doesn't seem too bad...

No no, I'm grateful for your offer. Let's not delay good
deeds. Let's proceed with the test at once.

(Riding a triangle horse for the first time, huh. I'm
nervous...)
--Karin straddled the triangle horse with nervousness.
\c[17]Karin Received 3000 Mon As A Reward For Participating In The Experiment!\c[0]

...I'm sorry. It's really scary after all, so I'll stop
here.

Every day, the experiments are so much fun. It's truly my
reason for living.

Oh, it seems you're out of smoke bombs? Take these newly
made smoke bombs with you.
